{"source_key":"sha256-563d56cafb5bb0a3ca15bfe1cd4cede0","record_index":14,"record_hash":"sha256:dfe6699987db4b2c5fc89c628e9e836b5a4f02cbce11bc33d3d01c628cfdb670","timestamp":"2026-06-07T13:10:07.692Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"The big lesson: don’t use agents as “faster typists.” Use them as workers inside a workflow you deliberately shape.\n\nWhat I’d apply:\n\n1. Keep `AGENTS.md` short and make it a map. Don’t cram every rule in there. Point to real docs, local conventions, test commands, architecture notes, and “how we do X” files. OpenAI explicitly found the giant-agent-manual approach rots fast.\n\n2. Turn repeated feedback into tooling. If you keep telling me “don’t do that,” it probably belongs in a lint, test, script, checklist, or scoped repo instruction. Taste should compound.\n\n3. Ask for end-to-end loops, not just patches. Better prompt: “reproduce the bug, capture evidence, fix it, run targeted validation, and tell me what changed.” That matches the article’s agent loop: reproduce, implement, validate, respond to feedback.\n\n4. Make the app legible to the agent. Logs, screenshots, browser control, dev servers, traces, test fixtures, local scripts: these are leverage. Anything I can’t inspect is basically folklore.\n\n5. Merge philosophy changes when fixes are cheap. Prefer small PRs and fast follow-ups over giant perfect branches. But only if the validation loop is strong enough.\n\n6. Garbage-collect continuously. Set aside regular “cleanup tiny inconsistencies” passes. AI repeats existing patterns, including bad ones. Bad patterns need to be removed before they become the house style.\n\nFor your workflow specifically: keep using me less like “write this code” and more like “own this change until it’s validated.” Give me the desired outcome, constraints, and validation bar; let me inspect, patch, test, and report. Then when you correct my judgment, we should encode that correction somewhere reusable.\n\nSource: OpenAI’s [Harness engineering: leveraging Codex in an agent-first world](https://openai.com/index/harness-engineering/).","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-06-07T13:10:07.692Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}